{"id":"project-LICHEN-pt5f","title":"secure.rs: PIV extraction lacks bounds check on OSCORE option length","description":"File: rust/lichen-node/src/secure.rs:191-193

The PIV (Partial IV) extraction from OSCORE option trusts the flags byte without validating option length:

```rust
let piv_len = (oscore_opt[0] & 0x07) as usize;
let request_piv = oscore_opt[1..1 + piv_len].to_vec();
```

If the OSCORE option is malformed (e.g., flags claim piv_len=7 but option only has 3 bytes), this will panic on slice bounds.

Impact: Malformed OSCORE messages could crash the secure stack.

Fix: Add bounds check:
```rust
let piv_len = (oscore_opt[0] & 0x07) as usize;
if oscore_opt.len() < 1 + piv_len {
    return Err(SecureError::CoapEncode);
}
let request_piv = oscore_opt[1..1 + piv_len].to_vec();
```","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:35:20.373323Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:35:20.373358Z"}

